Hayes TURNER, Appellant, v. UNITED STATES of America, Appellee. No. 11662. Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Oct. 30, 1946. Rehearing Denied Nov. 26, 1946. Grover C. Powell, of Atlanta, Ga., for appellant. Jack J. Gautier and Henry S. Barnes, Asst. U. S. Attys., both of Macon, Ga., for appellee.

Before HOLMES, WALLER, and LEE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The judgment of the Court below is affirmed.
